{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "quran-audio-api-collection",
		"name": "Quran Audio API",
		"description": "A RESTful API implementation for Quran audio recitations using PHP and Slim Framework 4.\n\n## Features\n- **Full CRUD Operations**: Complete Create, Read, Update, Delete functionality for Reciters, Recitations, and Audio Files\n- **Chapter Reciters**: Manage all available reciters with their details\n- **Recitations**: Manage recitation styles and metadata\n- **Audio Files**: Full management of audio files by chapter, juz, page, hizb, rub el hizb, or ayah\n- **Timestamps**: Word-level timing information for precise audio playback\n- **Pagination**: Efficient data retrieval with pagination support\n- **Multi-language**: Language parameter support for internationalization\n- **Grouped Routing**: Well-organized route structure in separate files\n\n## API Structure\n### Reciters Endpoints\n- GET /chapter-reciters - List all\n- GET /chapter-reciters/{id} - Get by ID\n- POST /chapter-reciters - Create\n- PUT /chapter-reciters/{id} - Update\n- DELETE /chapter-reciters/{id} - Delete\n\n### Recitations Endpoints\n- GET /recitations - List all\n- GET /recitations/{id} - Get by ID\n- POST /recitations - Create\n- PUT /recitations/{id} - Update\n- DELETE /recitations/{id} - Delete\n\n### Audio Files Endpoints\n- GET /audio-files/{id} - Get by ID\n- POST /audio-files - Create\n- PUT /audio-files/{id} - Update\n- DELETE /audio-files/{id} - Delete\n- Plus all existing resource endpoints for querying audio files",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
